text: Jaramillo is a corregimiento in Boquete District, Chiriquí Province, Panama. It has a land area of and had a population of 2,655 as of 2010, giving it a population density of . It was created by Law 58 of July 29, 1998, owing to the Declaration of Unconstitutionality of Law 1 of 1982. Its population as of 2000 was 2,047. ==References== Category:Corregimientos of Chiriquí Province
